"title": "5581: throne",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5581",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>An elevated seat occupied by a person with authority (e.g., a king). It symbolises the dignity, honour, sovereignty and the kingdom of the king whose seat it is. Supremely, these things belong to God himself.</p>\n<h2>A throne as an elevated seat</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs10:18-1Kgs10:19\">1KI 10:18–10:19</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr9:17-2Chr9:18\">2CH 9:17–9:18</a></p>\n<h2>A throne is occupied by a person with authority (usually a king)</h2>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:8\">PRO 20:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa14:9\">ISA 14:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:52\">LUK 1:52</a></p>\n<h3>Thrones of the kings of Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:46\">1KI 1:46</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs2:19\">1KI 2:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs7:7\">1KI 7:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:10\">1KI 22:10</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr18:9\">2CH 18:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs11:19\">2KI 11:19</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr23:20\">2CH 23:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer13:18\">JER 13:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:21\">ACT 12:21</a></p>\n<h3>Thrones of the kings of the nations</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod11:5\">EXO 11:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:29\">EXO 12:29</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth1:2\">EST 1:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth5:1\">EST 5:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer1:15\">JER 1:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek26:16\">EZK 26:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah3:6\">JON 3:6</a></p>\n<h2>A throne symbolises dignity and honour</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:40\">GEN 41:40</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:8\">1SA 2:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs25:28\">2KI 25:28</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer52:32\">JER 52:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa22:23\">ISA 22:23</a></p>\n<h2>A throne also symbolises sovereignty</h2>\n<h3>The royal power of earthly kings</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:13\">1KI 1:13</a></strong> <em>“Sit upon a throne” means “to exercise royal power”.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut17:181\">DEU 17:181</a>KI <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut1:17-Deut1:35\">1:17–1:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs2:4\">1KI 2:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs2:12\">1KI 2:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs2:24\">1KI 2:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs3:6\">1KI 3:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs5:5\">1KI 5:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:20\">1KI 8:20</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr6:10\">2CH 6:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:25\">1KI 8:25</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr6:16\">2CH 6:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs9:5\">1KI 9:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs10:9\">1KI 10:9</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr9:8\">2CH 9:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr28:5\">1CH 28:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:23\">1CH 29:23</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs16:11\">1KI 16:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs10:32\">2KI 10:32</a>KI <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs10:30\">10:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs15:12\">2KI 15:12</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps122:5\">PSA 122:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps132:11-Ps132:12\">PSA 132:11–132:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer22:2\">JER 22:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer22:30\">JER 22:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer29:16\">JER 29:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer33:17\">JER 33:17</a> <em>This verse is fulfilled ultimately in Jesus Christ (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:32\">Lk 1:32</a>)</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer43:10\">JER 43:10</a></p>\n<h3>Satan's throne on earth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:13\">REV 2:13</a></strong> <em>Satan is seen as “ruling” from Pergamum, the official centre of emperor worship in the province of Asia.</em></p>\n<h3>The beast's throne</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev13:2\">REV 13:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev16:10\">REV 16:10</a></p>\n<h3>The twenty-four elders are enthroned</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev4:4\">REV 4:4</a></strong> <em>The elders are thought to be representative of either the whole company of believers in heaven or an exalted angelic order.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev11:16\">REV 11:16</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ reigns from his eternal throne</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:7\">ISA 9:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech6:13\">ZEC 6:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:31\">MAT 25:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:32-Luke1:33\">LUK 1:32–1:33</a></p>\n<h3>Almighty God is seated in majesty on his holy throne</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod17:16\">EXO 17:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps47:8\">PSA 47:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb8:1\">HEB 8:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:21\">HEB 12:21</a>KI <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb22:19\">22:19</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr18:18\">2CH 18:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek1:26\">EZK 1:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek10:1\">EZK 10:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:9\">DAN 7:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev4:2-Rev4:10\">REV 4:2–4:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:1\">REV 5:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:7\">REV 5:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:13\">REV 5:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:10\">REV 7:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:15\">REV 7:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:4\">REV 19:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:5\">REV 21:5</a>PSA <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev9:4-Rev9:10\">9:4–9:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps11:4\">PSA 11:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer49:38\">JER 49:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:16\">REV 6:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:11-Rev20:12\">REV 20:11–20:12</a>REV <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:11\">7:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev8:3\">REV 8:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev14:3\">REV 14:3</a>REV <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:4\">1:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev4:5\">REV 4:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:9\">REV 7:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev12:5\">REV 12:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev16:17\">REV 16:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:3\">REV 21:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:1\">REV 22:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:3\">REV 22:3</a></p>\n<h2>A throne symbolises a kingdom</h2>\n<h3>The kingdoms of earthly kings</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam3:10\">2SA 3:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:37\">1KI 1:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:47\">1KI 1:47</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:28\">PRO 20:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:5\">PRO 25:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov29:14\">PRO 29:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:36\">DAN 4:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:20\">DAN 5:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag2:222\">HAG 2:222</a>SA <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag7:13-Hag7:16\">7:13–7:16</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr17:12-1Chr17:14\">1CH 17:12–17:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs2:33\">1KI 2:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs2:45\">1KI 2:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs9:5\">1KI 9:5</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr7:18\">2CH 7:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr22:10\">1CH 22:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:4\">PSA 89:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:29\">PSA 89:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:36\">PSA 89:36</a></p>\n<h3>The unseen kingdom of God's righteous rule</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:14\">PSA 89:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps93:2\">PSA 93:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps97:2\">PSA 97:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps103:19\">PSA 103:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam5:19\">LAM 5:19</a></p>\n<h2>The ark of the covenant seen as God's throne</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam4:4\">1SA 4:4</a></strong> <em>God was understood to be enthroned between the cherubim (i.e., upon the lid, or “mercy seat”) of the ark of the covenant.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam6:2\">2SA 6:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs19:15\">2KI 19:15</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa37:16\">ISA 37:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps80:1\">PSA 80:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps99:1\">PSA 99:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:12\">JER 17:12</a></p>\n<h2>Jerusalem is also called God's throne</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:17\">JER 3:17</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Heaven described as God's throne</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps2:4\">PSA 2:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps123:1\">PSA 123:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:22\">ISA 40:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:34\">MAT 5:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:22\">MAT 23:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:49\">ACT 7:49</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa66:1\">ISA 66:1</a></p>\n<h2>God's throne is a throne of grace</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:16\">HEB 4:16</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Believers share in the heavenly reign of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:28\">MAT 19:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:30\">LUK 22:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:12\">2TI 2:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:21\">REV 3:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:4\">REV 20:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:6\">REV 20:6</a></p>",
